58.0	Argyria	Argyria	Argyria (ISV from Greek: ἄργυρος argyros silver + -ia) is a condition caused by improper exposure to chemical forms of the element silver, silver dust, or silver compounds. The most dramatic symptom of argyria is that the skin becomes blue or bluish-grey colored. Argyria may be found as generalized argyria or local argyria. Argyrosis is the corresponding condition related to the eye.	http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/3/38/Argyria_2.jpg/220px-Argyria_2.jpg
